        "# 1. Create a synthetic dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "# Quiz_Average (0â€“100), Time_Spent_Minutes (daily average), Problems_Solved (total), Pass_Class (0/1)\n",
        "\n",
        "np.random.seed(42)  # Set seed so results are repeatable\n",
        "\n",
        "n_samples = 50  # Number of students in our synthetic dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate random quiz averages between 0 and 100\n",
        "quiz_average = np.random.normal(loc=70, scale=15, size=n_samples)\n",
        "quiz_average = np.clip(quiz_average, 0, 100)  # Ensure values stay between 0 and 100\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate time spent (in minutes per day), e.g., between 10 and 180 minutes\n",
        "time_spent = np.random.normal(loc=60, scale=20, size=n_samples)\n",
        "time_spent = np.clip(time_spent, 10, 180)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate number of problems solved, e.g., between 0 and 200\n",
        "problems_solved = np.random.poisson(lam=50, size=n_samples)  # Poisson for count data\n",
        "\n",
        "# Now define Pass_Class based on a simple rule plus some noise:\n",
        "# Students with higher quiz_average and more time/probs are more likely to pass.\n",
        "# We compute a \"score\" and then threshold it to get 0/1.\n",
        "\n",
        "score = (0.04 * quiz_average) + (0.01 * time_spent) + (0.02 * problems_solved) + np.random.normal(0, 2, n_samples)\n",
        "\n",
        "# np.random.normal(0, 2, n_samples) is random noise added\n",
        "\n",
        "# Apply threshold: if score > some value, mark as pass (1), else fail (0)\n",
        "pass_class = (score > 5).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Put everything into a pandas DataFrame (table-like structure)\n",
        "data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Quiz_Average': quiz_average,\n",
        "    'Time_Spent_Minutes': time_spent,\n",
        "    'Problems_Solved': problems_solved,\n",
        "    'Pass_Class': pass_class\n",
        "})"
      ],
